Step 5: Significance of the Reduction

While 0.382 Ã— 10Â²Â² J is a significant amount of energy, it's important to assess it in the context of the total heat generated in the HAD 2.0 model. From the initial estimate of 8.4 Ã— 10Â²â¸ J/year generated by the accelerated nuclear decay, 
